    base:desc "Control commands are issued from the Digital Twin via the Actuation FE components (Motor Actuation, Steering Servo Actuation FE). These commands are serialized and unit‑converted by the Data Translation FE, then transmitted over UDP/Wi‑Fi to the corresponding physical actuators. Feedback signals (e.g., actuator state) are routed through the same Data Translation FE and the ROS 2 network back to the Digital Twin for real‑time status monitoring and confirmation of command execution."
