instance dt_constellation : DTDFVocab:Constellation [
    base:desc "The architecture follows ISO 23247 Reference Architecture, implementing each Functional Entity (FE) as an individual ROS 2 package containing one or more ROS 2 nodes. The Physical Twin Entity hosts the hardware resources (compute, sensors, actuators) and implements lower‑level automotive functions such as point‑cloud clustering and tracking. The Digital Twin Entity gathers data‑management and control‑mechanism services, while the User Entity contains the User Interface FE, subdivided into 3D Visualization and Control Panel sub‑components. Each FE is deployed on a distinct hardware node, yielding a decentralized deployment model. Coordination is achieved through ROS 2 topics and services, adhering to the ISO 23247 entity‑based structure and ensuring clear ownership and modular communication across the twin’s functional layers."
